Page10:
The seizure cycle is divided into different stages:

Interictal Phase (Non-seizure state) â€“ A period that lasts for several hours before or after a seizure.
Preictal Phase (Pre-seizure state) â€“ The critical time window before a seizure occurs.
Seizure Phase â€“ The period when the seizure is actively happening.
Postictal Phase (Recovery state) â€“ A phase following the seizure where brain activity stabilizes.
ğŸ“Œ Preictal Subdivision for Seizure Prediction
To enhance seizure prediction accuracy, the preictal state is further divided into three smaller segments:

Pre I (40-60 minutes before seizure)
Pre II (20-40 minutes before seizure)
Pre III (0-20 minutes before seizure)
This segmentation allows more precise classification of seizure onset, enabling early detection and intervention.

